label: AB6C_tP32_86_c_3g_d-001
title: NaSb(OH)$_{6}$ ($J1_{11}$) Structure
comments:
The atomic positions were originally determined using setting 1 of space group $P4_{2}/n$ \#86.  We used FINDSYM to change the origin to setting 2. 
 The sites labeled ``O'' are actually OH radicals. 
 Although the replacement of fluorine by OH does not affect the shape of the Sb-(F,OH)$_{6}$ ions, it has a profound effect on the structure, as can be seen by looking at \href{current_web_home_dir/A6BC_cP32_205_d_a_b-001}{NaSbF$_{6}$} and \href{current_web_home_dir/A6BC_hP16_163_i_b_c-001}{NaSbF$_{4}$(OH)$_{2}$ ($J1_{12}$)}.
